http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Action-plan-sought-on-plastic-ban/article14013157.ece

Taking strong exception to ‘non-enforcement’ of Plastic Waste Management and Handling Rules 2011, National Green Tribunal has directed Odisha government to submit action taken report on prohibition on plastic use.“The Chief Secretary, Odisha has filed a status report. On perusal of the affidavit it appears that coordination committee for effective implementation and enforcement of Plastic Waste Management and Handling Rules 2011, was constituted in January 2013 and a notification has also been issued to that effect,” NGT said in its order.The first meeting coordination committee was held on February 25, 2013. The NGT has served notice on different departments of the State government to explain action taken on decision taken by coordination committee within four weeks.